FBIS4-27963 "dreas109_d_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 South Korea DPRK UN Envoy Confirms Missile Test Firing DPRK UN Envoy Confirms Missile Test Firing SK0606232394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2100 GMT 6 Jun 94 SK0606232394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [YONHAP Report from Geneva] [Text] North Korea made it clear yesterday hat it had test fired a missile in the East Sea, stressing that it was a routine exercise. In a news conference, (Han Cha-won), North Korea's permanent representative to the United Nations, said that the test firing of the missile was a regular and routine exercise and that North Korea's missiles are completely for defensive purposes. The Japanese and U.S. Governments revealed at the end of last month that North Korea had tested a missile -- an improved model of China's Silk Worm missiles. Until now, North Korea has not confirmed that it had test fired a missile.
